--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, our spring moves went exactly as planned - excellent coordination. For fall, I intend to move F ION to TUN and A APU to support, securing that neutral center. My A TYR will move to TRI to take that supply center - I hope you'll allow this peacefully as part of our arrangement, or alternatively I can move TYR to VIE to support you against Russia if you prefer. What are your intentions for fall? I want to ensure we don't clash in the Adriatic or Balkans."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, our arrangement holds well. I'm moving F ION to TUN this fall - no threat to you. Greece remains contested - I'd prefer we agree: I take Greece with F ION support from AEG, you consolidate Bulgaria and Rumania. We can divide the eastern Med profitably if we avoid fighting each other. What are your fall intentions? Let's confirm no Aegean interference from either side."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, the western front remains quiet between us - good. I'm focused entirely on Tunisia and the eastern Mediterranean this fall. I have no designs on Marseilles or Piedmont. I'd welcome continued non-aggression and perhaps future coordination against common threats. What are your fall plans?"}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The arrangement continues to serve us both well. This fall I intend A KIE-HOL and A RUH-BEL, with F DEN moving to support or toward SWE. I expect you're moving on NWY - we should coordinate so neither of us steps on the other's toes. HOL and BEL are mine; NWY and the northern seas are yours. France in BUR is a concern for both of us - if you can pressure them from the channel, I'll squeeze from the east. Let's keep this partnership productive."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, I note your army sits in BUR adjacent to my RUH. I have no hostile intentions toward you - my focus is entirely on HOL and BEL this fall. I propose we avoid conflict: I take HOL, you take BEL, and we both profit. A RUH will move to HOL or BEL - I'd prefer BEL goes to you if you move there first, but I need HOL secured. If you're willing to coordinate, we can both gain two centers this fall without fighting each other. What do you say?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I trust your moves are going well in the east. I want to flag that England is positioning aggressively in the north - F NTH is a threat to both NWY and potentially STP long-term. I'm focused westward this fall, but I'd encourage you to think carefully about England's naval dominance. A strong Russia in the north keeps England honest. Meanwhile, I have no designs on your western territories - let's maintain our understanding."}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Excellent opening - our positions are exactly as planned. This fall I intend to move F NTH to NWY (securing that center) and F ENG to BEL. I'd ask that you move A RUH to BEL to support my fleet's entry, or alternatively take HOL with A KIE while I take BEL uncontested. Either way, we split the neutrals cleanly and both gain a build. Confirm your intentions for HOL and BEL so we don't accidentally clash. The Anglo-German partnership is proving its worth already."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, I want to be direct: I'm moving F NTH to NWY this fall and F ENG toward BEL. I have no designs on your home centers or Iberia - Spain and Portugal are yours to develop. I'd prefer we maintain the current understanding and avoid any friction in the Channel. If you're eyeing BEL, we should discuss - I'm willing to consider arrangements that benefit us both, but I need clarity on your intentions before I commit my fleet elsewhere."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I trust your fleet moved to BOT as planned - that keeps the Baltic arrangement intact. I'm taking NWY this fall with F NTH, which should be uncontested given our understanding. I'm watching the eastern situation with interest - the Austro-Turkish contest looks fierce. If you need any diplomatic support or coordination against a common threat, Britain is a reliable partner. Let me know your fall intentions."}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Your fleet in the Black Sea is a direct provocation. I hold RUM with F RUM and have A UKR ready to reinforce SEV. If you move against me, I will coordinate with AUT to crush you from both sides. However, I prefer cooperation: you take GRE and keep BUL, I keep RUM and SEV, and we divide the Balkans peacefully. Confirm your intentions immediately - I need to know if you are friend or enemy before I issue orders.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "We bounced in GAL last spring - a waste for both of us. I propose we formalize a border: GAL belongs to Austria, I keep RUM and will not contest BUD or VIE. In return, I need you to turn your forces against TUR - specifically, move A SER toward BUL to pressure Turkey from the west while I press from the north. Turkey is the common threat. If we coordinate now, we can both expand at Turkey's expense. What do you say?"}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Good spring - you've positioned well in the west. I'm moving F BOT toward SWE this fall. I'd appreciate you not contesting SWE - it's naturally in my sphere and I have no interest in DEN or your Baltic position. In return, I'll stay out of PRU and SIL entirely. Let's keep our non-aggression solid and both focus on our natural expansion zones. Confirm you're not moving into SWE."}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, our spring moves went exactly as discussed - F BRE to MAO as promised, keeping the Channel clear. Now for fall: I intend A SPA to POR and F MAO to SPA(SC) to lock in Iberia. I need BEL for France this fall - A BUR is positioned to take it. I ask that you not contest BEL; in return, France will not challenge your position in NOR or HOL. We can divide the low countries cleanly: BEL to France, HOL to Germany or neutral, NOR to England. A strong Anglo-French understanding keeps Germany in check. Confirm BEL is mine and we have a deal.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I note you moved A MUN to RUH rather than BUR - wise, and I appreciate the restraint. My A BUR is positioned for BEL this fall, not MUN. I propose we formalize this: France takes BEL, Germany takes HOL. We both gain a supply center without conflict, and we can coordinate to keep England from dominating the north. I have no designs on MUN or RUH if you stay out of BEL and BUR. Respond and let's make this concrete - a Franco-German understanding benefits us both enormously in 1902."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, our arrangement continues to serve us both well. I'm securing Iberia this fall and moving on BEL. I encourage you to press Austria hard via TYR toward TRI or VIE - Austria is vulnerable with A VIE bounced out of GAL. A weakened Austria benefits both of us. I will stay entirely out of PIE and the Mediterranean for now. Keep me informed of your moves and let's coordinate to ensure neither of us gets squeezed."}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Our arrangement has worked perfectly - you're positioned well in the south and I've secured Serbia. I intend to move F ALB - GRE this fall to take that supply center. I'd ask that F ION not contest GRE - it's clearly in my sphere. In return, I'll continue to respect Venice and the Adriatic. I'm also moving A VIE toward BUD to free up for a build, and looking at RUM as a target. Let's keep this cooperation going - we're both well-positioned if we don't fight each other."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Excellent coordination last spring - you have BUL secured and I have SER. Now let's coordinate for fall: I plan F ALB - GRE and want to ensure we don't collide. If you're moving A BUL toward somewhere else (CON or RUM), that clears the path nicely. I'm also eyeing RUM - Russia's F RUM is a problem for both of us. If you can pressure RUM from BUL while I push from SER or BUD, we can squeeze Russia out of the Balkans entirely. What are your fall intentions?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "We bounced in Galicia as I warned we would. I have no interest in a prolonged conflict with Russia - my focus is the Balkans and southeastern expansion. I propose we formalize a non-aggression pact: GAL remains a buffer zone with neither of us entering, and I won't threaten WAR or UKR. In exchange, I need you to pull F RUM back - it's sitting on an unowned supply center that I consider within my natural sphere. If you're reasonable about RUM, we can find a stable arrangement. Otherwise I'll be forced to coordinate with Turkey against you."}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, our spring coordination worked perfectly - you hold SER, I hold BUL, and we've cleanly divided the Balkans. Now for autumn: I intend to push F BLA into RUM this fall, taking that center from Russia. I need you to hold SER steady and not interfere with RUM - in return, I will not contest GRE if you want to move F ALB there. Russia is our common enemy; they bounced your GAL move and hold RUM aggressively. Let's coordinate to squeeze them from both sides. Confirm you'll leave RUM to me and I'll support your Balkan expansion."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, our understanding holds - I have BUL secured and am eyeing RUM this autumn via the Black Sea. I have no interest in the Aegean or Greece - those are yours to take with F ION. I'd suggest moving F ION to GRE this fall for a clean capture. We remain friendly neighbors with no conflicting interests. Just keep your fleet out of the Eastern Med for now and we'll have no problems."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I want to be direct: my F BLA is positioned and I intend to take RUM this autumn - it is an unowned center and I have the stronger position. However, I have no interest in SEV or ARM, and I am not your enemy in the north. You have WAR, UKR, BOT - plenty of room to grow westward against Austria and Germany. Let us agree: RUM goes to Turkey, you focus on GAL and Scandinavia, and we avoid a costly war that only benefits Austria and Italy. I am offering you a clean boundary - Black Sea as a shared waterway, no attacks on SEV. Accept this and we can coexist profitably.'}]
INFO:main:Negotiation sub-round 2/2
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "Confirmed: A KIE moves to HOL, A RUH moves to BEL to support your F ENG entry into BEL - wait, actually I need to reconsider. If you're taking BEL with F ENG, I'll take HOL with A KIE and move A RUH to HOL as support, or A RUH to BEL to support you in. Let's be precise: F NTH-NWY, F ENG-BEL, A KIE-HOL, A RUH supports F ENG-BEL. This gives us both a clean gain. F DEN moves to SWE or holds. Confirm this exact coordination and we both build in winter."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, we have a deal - you take BEL, I take HOL. My orders will be A KIE-HOL and A RUH supports your move into BEL (or holds to avoid conflict). F DEN stays out of your way. This Franco-German understanding is the foundation for 1902 cooperation. England is the long-term threat to both of us - once we've secured our neutrals, we should discuss how to check their naval dominance together. For now: BEL is yours, HOL is mine, no conflict."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, confirmed - I am not contesting SWE. F DEN will move to support or hold, not to SWE. That center is yours to take with F BOT. Our non-aggression stands firm and I have no interest in PRU or SIL. Focus your energies east and south - Austria and Turkey are your natural rivals. I'll keep England occupied in the west. A strong Russia and a strong Germany is the natural order of things."}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Your offer is rejected. F RUM stays - I took that center and I will hold it. You cannot take RUM with F BLA alone while I have F RUM there plus A UKR in support range. Any attack on RUM means immediate war: I will move A UKR to SEV, coordinate with AUT to press BUL from SER, and make your position untenable. The smart move for you is GRE and SMY expansion southward. Accept the reality: RUM is mine, BUL is yours, and we maintain a cold peace. Attack me and you lose everything.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, your threat to coordinate with Turkey against me is noted - and it tells me you are not serious about diplomacy. Turkey just told me they intend to take RUM and push north. If you side with them, you hand Turkey the Balkans and eventually face them alone. My offer stands: GAL is yours as a buffer, I keep RUM, and we both press Turkey together - you move A SER toward BUL, I hold RUM and threaten BLA. This is the only arrangement that benefits Austria. Choose wisely: ally with me against Turkey now, or watch Turkey grow until it's too late."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Agreed on England - their naval position in NTH is a long-term threat to both of us. I'm moving F BOT to SWE this fall to secure that center. I confirm I will stay entirely out of PRU, SIL, and your Baltic sphere. Our non-aggression holds firm. Focus west - I'll handle the east. If England becomes aggressive toward you, I'm open to deeper coordination."}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, let's be precise about fall orders: I will move F BLA - RUM to capture that center, and A BUL will support F BLA into RUM. This means A BUL stays in place supporting the fleet move. You should move F ALB - GRE for a clean capture - I will not interfere. If you want to pressure Russia from SER toward RUM as well, that only helps, but my support from BUL is committed to the fleet move. A CON will move to SMY or hold - no threat to you. We are aligned: Russia is the target this autumn."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your threat to coordinate with Austria against me is empty - Austria is already coordinating WITH me against you. You are surrounded. I am taking RUM this autumn; my fleet and army are positioned to do so with certainty. Your only rational choice is to accept this loss gracefully and redirect your energy westward against Germany and Austria in the north, where you have real opportunities. Fight me and you lose RUM AND weaken yourself for the western powers to exploit. Accept the boundary and we can stabilize. The decision is yours, but my orders are already set.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, confirmed - no Aegean interference from me. You take TUN this fall, excellent. On Greece: I have no claim there, it is yours to take when ready. My F BLA moves to RUM, A BUL supports that move and stays put. We remain fully aligned with no conflicting interests. Let's both grow our empires and stay out of each other's way - the eastern Mediterranean can be divided profitably between us once Russia is contained."}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, I must be direct: moving A TYR to TRI is a betrayal of our agreement and I will not accept it. Trieste is my home center and was explicitly off-limits in our arrangement. If you move on TRI, I will treat it as a declaration of war and coordinate with Turkey against you immediately. However, if you honor our pact - TYR stays out of TRI, ION goes to TUN as you planned - we remain strong allies. I'm moving F ALB to GRE this fall and A VIE to BUD to prepare a build. I need TRI safe. Make the right choice."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, confirmed: I will move F ALB to GRE this fall and leave RUM to you - your F BLA push into RUM has my full support. I will hold A SER steady to protect BUL's flank and ensure you can take RUM cleanly. One warning: Italy is threatening to move A TYR into TRI, which would destabilize my position. If that happens I may need to redirect A VIE to TRI defense rather than BUD. But assuming Italy behaves, our Balkan coordination proceeds perfectly. Russia is the target - let's squeeze them together."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your proposal is interesting but I cannot turn against Turkey now - we have a working arrangement and Turkey is moving on RUM this fall, which actually serves my interests by weakening you in the Balkans. Here is my genuine offer: I will not move into GAL this fall, and I will not support any attack on WAR or UKR. In exchange, accept that RUM will fall to Turkey and focus your energy westward. If you fight both Turkey and me simultaneously, you will lose the south entirely. A stable GAL border benefits us both - but RUM is gone regardless.'}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I've heard your request on Greece - I understand your interest, but F ION is better positioned to take Greece this fall and I need that center for my build. Here's my proposal: I take Greece with F ION, you take Rumania via your position. I will move A TYR to VIE to support you if needed, or hold in TYR as a buffer - I will NOT move to TRI this fall. This gives us both a build and keeps our cooperation intact. If you contest Greece with F ALB, we both risk losing it to Turkey or bouncing each other, which only helps our enemies. Let's be smart: I take GRE, you take RUM, we both grow. Confirm and I'll keep TYR peaceful."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, confirmed - I'm moving F ION to GRE this fall for a clean capture, exactly as you suggest. You take BUL and push for RUM via Black Sea. We have no conflicting interests this turn. I'll keep my fleet out of Eastern Med and AEG beyond GRE. Let's both build and grow - we can discuss dividing the Balkans and eastern Mediterranean profitably next year. Our partnership is working well."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, agreed on continued non-aggression - your focus on BEL and Iberia is noted. I'm taking TUN and GRE this fall for two builds. Regarding Austria: I'm keeping A TYR in a flexible position but not attacking TRI this fall - I want to build trust with Austria a bit longer before turning. However, if you're pressing from the west and I push from TYR next year, Austria collapses quickly. Let's stay in close contact for 1902 coordination - a coordinated Franco-Italian squeeze on Austria could be devastating."}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, I hear you - F ENG moving toward BEL is a problem for us both if we end up bouncing each other and handing Germany an easy path. Here is my final offer: I will move A BUR to BEL this fall. If you support me into BEL with F ENG, we guarantee it falls to France and you keep your fleet free for NWY and the north. Alternatively, if you insist on taking BEL yourself, we will bounce and both lose a center to Germany's benefit. The rational choice is clear: BEL to France, NOR and HOL to England and Germany respectively. I am moving A BUR to BEL regardless - the question is whether you help me or we waste both our moves. Choose cooperation."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, we are aligned - France takes BEL, Germany takes HOL. I am moving A BUR to BEL this fall. England is threatening to contest BEL with F ENG, which would bounce me. If you can move A RUH to support my A BUR into BEL, we guarantee France gets it and England is blocked - then you take HOL uncontested. This is the optimal outcome for both of us. England grabbing BEL would be a disaster for Franco-German interests. Support A BUR into BEL and we both profit handsomely this fall. Confirm and let's execute."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, glad we remain aligned. I am securing BEL this fall while locking in Iberia - France will have 5 centers by year end if all goes well. I strongly encourage you to push A TYR toward TRI or VIE - Austria is exposed and this is the moment to strike. A weakened Austria in 1902 opens enormous opportunities for both of us in the Balkans and Adriatic. Stay the course, keep pressure on Austria, and France will remain entirely out of your sphere. We are natural partners for now.'}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Confirmed - our plans align perfectly. You take HOL with A KIE and BEL with A RUH, I take NWY with F NTH. F DEN can move to SKA or support as needed. One concern: France is demanding BEL for themselves with A BUR positioned to take it. If A RUH moves to BEL, that directly contests France - which I support, as it keeps them contained. I'll move F ENG to support your A RUH into BEL if needed, or I can move F ENG to MAO to pressure France from the west. Either way, Germany gets BEL and France gets nothing. The Anglo-German partnership holds - let's execute cleanly."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, I appreciate the transparency, but I must be honest: Germany is already moving A RUH to BEL this fall, and I cannot stop that without breaking my existing arrangement with Berlin. My F ENG is committed to supporting German moves in the low countries as part of our partnership. I strongly advise you redirect A BUR elsewhere - perhaps toward MUN or PIC - rather than clash with Germany over BEL and lose the unit. Portugal and Spain are secure for you; that's two builds. Don't overextend into a contested BEL and risk your army. A France focused on Iberia and the Mediterranean is a France that thrives - and one Britain can work with long-term."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, glad our arrangement holds. I'm taking NWY this fall as planned - F NTH to NWY. I note Austria has SER and is positioned strongly in the Balkans while Turkey holds BUL and BLA. The Austro-Turkish contest will define the east. Britain's interest is in a balanced continent - we don't want any single power dominating. If Austria grows too strong, I'd be open to coordinating pressure. Keep me informed of your intentions in Scandinavia and the south - I want to ensure our interests remain complementary rather than competitive."}]
