--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, the situation has changed dramatically - you've retaken Trieste and I respect that. I have no interest in a prolonged war with you when there are better targets available. My fleet in Tunis will hold or move toward the western Med, and my army in Venice will not threaten Trieste this fall. I propose a genuine ceasefire: you focus on the Balkans and Russia/Turkey, I focus on the western Mediterranean and building my fleet strength. Russia now sits in Budapest - that's your real threat, not me. Let's not bleed each other while Russia and Turkey grow strong."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, Austria has retaken Trieste and their fleet sits in the Aegean - that's a direct threat to both of us. I'm moving to consolidate Tunis this fall and build a new fleet. I propose we coordinate against Austria: you push from Greece toward the Aegean and I'll eventually press from the Adriatic. Austria with F AEG is dangerous for your Aegean ambitions. What are your plans this fall - are you moving on Rumania or pressing Austria?"}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, Austria has pushed me back to Venice and Tunis - I need to rebuild. I'm taking Tunis this fall and building a fleet. I have no designs on Marseilles or Piedmont - you have my word. I'd appreciate confirmation you're keeping F WES out of Tyrrhenian and away from Tunis. In return, I'll support your western ambitions and stay out of your sphere. What's your plan against England and Germany this fall?"}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "The spring moves went well for both of us - I retook Trieste, you secured Sevastopol and Greece. Now let's coordinate for autumn. I propose: F AEG moves to BUL/SC or supports your A GRE, while A SER holds or moves to BUL. Russia's F RUM and A BUD (which is now YOUR A BUD, I see) are the key threats. I want RUM eventually - can we coordinate to take it? I'll support your moves against Russia if you support mine. What are your intentions for CON and GRE this fall?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your A BUD is sitting in MY supply center. I expect you to vacate it immediately - move it to GAL or RUM. If you do not, I will take aggressive action to dislodge it. I have no quarrel with Russia if you respect Austrian territory, but occupying BUD is an act of war. I am prepared to coordinate with Turkey against you if you force my hand. What will it be - peaceful withdrawal or conflict?'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, I've retaken Trieste as you can see - this is my home center and non-negotiable. However, I have no desire for further conflict with you. I propose we both focus elsewhere: you expand in the western Mediterranean and Africa, I focus on the Balkans and Russia. A VEN-TYR or similar westward moves from you would reassure me. In return, I will not threaten Venice or move into the Adriatic. Let's formalize this - what are your autumn intentions?"}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Kaiser, let us be direct. You hold BEL and MUN is now mine - we are at an impasse that benefits neither of us. I propose a clean settlement: I keep MUN, you keep BEL, and we establish a firm border along RUH/BUR. France has no interest in pushing further east if Germany respects this line. My army in MUN can move to BUR or BOH - your choice of direction signals your intent. England is the real threat to both of us with their fleet in NTH and ENG. A Franco-German understanding against English naval dominance serves us both. What say you?'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, Germany now holds BEL and sits in MUN - they are growing dangerously. I have A MUN positioned to threaten BER or KIE directly. If you move F NTH to support pressure on GER from the north while I push from MUN, we can crack Germany open and divide their centers. I propose: I take KIE or BER, you take HOL or BEL. This is the moment to act before Germany consolidates. Are you willing to coordinate a joint strike on Germany this fall?'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Friend, our arrangement continues to serve us both well. I intend to press Germany from MUN this fall - their position is overextended. I ask only that you maintain pressure on Austria to keep them occupied and unable to assist Germany. If Austria is tied down, Germany falls faster and we both benefit from the redistribution. What are your plans for this fall? I want to ensure we remain coordinated.'}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Your fleet sits in Sevastopol - my supply center. This is unacceptable and will be corrected. I have F RUM and A UKR positioned to retake SEV. I am offering you one chance to withdraw F SEV to BLA voluntarily this turn. If you do, I will not pursue further aggression against you and we can discuss a partition of the Balkans - BUL and GRE are yours, I want BUD and VIE. If you refuse, I will drive you out by force and coordinate with Austria against your Anatolian centers. Your choice.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, the situation has changed dramatically. Turkey has seized Sevastopol - my home center. I propose an immediate ceasefire between us. I hold BUD currently and you hold SER - let us not waste strength fighting each other while Turkey expands. I propose: I withdraw A BUD to GAL, you leave SER and VIE unmolested, and we both turn against Turkey. I can push F RUM toward BUL while you attack GRE with F AEG. Together we can dismantle Turkey's Balkan position. I am willing to let you have SER and BUL if we coordinate now. Respond with your intentions."}, {'recipients': ['ENG', 'GER'], 'body': 'Gentlemen, the northern front remains stable and I intend to keep it that way. F SWE will hold position. I am focused entirely on the south where Turkey has seized Sevastopol. I have no designs on Scandinavia or the Baltic beyond what I already hold. Germany, DEN is yours if you want it - I will not contest it. England, NWY remains yours. Let us maintain our mutual non-aggression and prosper.'}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I must be direct with you: last season I moved A BUL to GRE while your F GRE vacated to AEG - I took the opportunity and I won't pretend otherwise. However, I propose we move past this and focus on our shared enemy Russia. RUS now holds BUD, RUM, and SEV - they are the dominant power threatening both of us. I propose: you push A SER toward BUD to reclaim it, and I will move F SEV toward RUM to pressure Russia from the south. We can divide the Russian centers between us. I have no interest in TRI or VIE - my targets are RUM and the Russian coast. Let's not waste energy fighting each other when Russia is the real threat."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, you now hold BUD, RUM, SEV, SWE - six centers and growing. You are the largest power on the board and every other nation will soon recognize this threat. I hold SEV and GRE - I am not your primary enemy. I propose a temporary arrangement: I will not attack RUM this season if you withdraw A UKR away from the front. We can establish a boundary at RUM/SEV and both focus our energies elsewhere. Continued conflict between us only benefits Austria and Italy. What terms would you accept for a ceasefire?'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, you now hold TRI and TUN - well positioned. Austria has F AEG threatening both of us in the eastern Mediterranean. I propose we coordinate: I will keep A GRE positioned to pressure AUT's Serbian position, and you should consider moving into the Adriatic or Aegean to challenge Austria's fleet. AUT is overextended holding SER, TRI, VIE, and now threatening the sea lanes. A joint TUR-ITA pressure on Austria would benefit us both greatly. What are your intentions this season?"}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "The BEL situation has become a stalemate that benefits neither of us. I propose we finally resolve it cleanly: I will move F NTH to BEL with F ENG supporting, giving England BEL. In exchange, I will actively support German expansion eastward - specifically, I will not contest HOL and will support your moves against France or Russia as you see fit. Germany already holds HOL and DEN is uncontested - you're in a strong position. Let England take BEL and we formalize our alliance properly. What do you say? I need your confirmation that you will NOT move A BEL or contest this, and in return I offer full Anglo-German cooperation going forward."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, I want to be direct with you. Germany holds BEL with A BEL and has SKA positioned in the north - they are becoming the dominant continental power. I am prepared to work with France against German expansion. My F NTH can threaten the North Sea approaches while your forces press from the south. I propose: England takes BEL this fall (F NTH-BEL, F ENG supports), and in 1903 we coordinate against Germany together. Your fleet in WES is well-positioned for the Mediterranean, and I have no interest in your Atlantic coast. Let's formalize an Anglo-French understanding - Germany is the real threat to both of us."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, the northern situation is stable between us and I appreciate that. I want to flag that Germany now holds BEL, SKA, and HOL - they are growing rapidly and will become a threat to both our interests. I intend to take BEL this fall. I ask only that you continue to keep F SWE out of NTH/SKA, and I will continue to respect your northern holdings. A strong England checking German naval power is in Russia's interest as much as mine."}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Comrade, the situation has shifted dramatically. France has seized Munich - my home center! This is an act of war I cannot ignore. I must retake MUN immediately. I propose we coordinate: I will push A BEL toward BUR and A HOL toward RUH to squeeze France from the north. Meanwhile, I need your assurance that you will not exploit my western focus - keep your units away from SIL and PRU. In return, I will support your position in the east and stay entirely out of Scandinavia. F SKA will move to DEN to secure that neutral, nothing more. France is becoming dangerously large with 5 centers - this threatens us both eventually.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, France has taken Munich and now sits at 5 centers with A MUN threatening to build further. This is a direct threat to both of us. I propose we coordinate against France immediately: I will move A BEL to BUR and A HOL to RUH, driving toward MUN to retake my home center. You should pressure France from the west - move into MAO or threaten BRE/PAR. If we split France between us now, we can each gain significantly. I am willing to let BEL remain contested for now - the priority is crushing France before they snowball. What can you commit to against France this turn?'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, France has stabbed me by taking Munich - 5 centers now and growing. I am pivoting all forces to retake MUN: A BEL to BUR, A HOL to RUH, building pressure from the north. I need you to hold firm in the south and not let Italy or Russia exploit the chaos. Our axis remains valuable - once I deal with France, German strength will be fully available to support Austrian ambitions in the Balkans. Can you confirm your current intentions regarding Italy and Russia? I want to ensure we are not working at cross-purposes.'}]
INFO:main:Negotiation sub-round 2/2
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I accept your proposal. This fall: A VEN holds in Venice (no threat to Trieste), F TUN holds in Tunis. I am not moving into the Adriatic or toward your positions. Russia in Budapest is the existential threat to you - I suggest you focus A SER toward BUD to reclaim it. I will not interfere in the Balkans. Let us both grow stronger against our real enemies.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, I agree Austria's F AEG is a long-term problem for both of us. This fall I am consolidating Tunis and holding Venice - I need to build a fleet before I can challenge Austria at sea. Next year I will have a new fleet and can press into the Adriatic or Ionian to threaten Austria's position. For now, keep A GRE positioned to pressure Serbia - that pins Austria down perfectly. We coordinate properly in 1903 when I have the naval strength to back it up."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, understood - I will maintain pressure on Austria from Venice to keep them occupied and unable to assist Germany. A VEN stays positioned as a threat to Trieste, which should keep Austrian attention eastward rather than northward toward your MUN position. My F TUN consolidates this fall. Push hard on Germany - MUN is yours to keep and HOL/BEL are ripe. I remain your reliable southern partner.'}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I hear your concern about France in MUN, and I agree they must be checked. Here is my firm commitment: I will move F NTH to BEL this fall, taking that center for England. You should move A BEL to BUR to directly threaten France's position - this is the coordinated strike we need. I will support pressure on France from the north while you push from BEL into BUR. Do NOT hold A BEL in place - move it to BUR and let me take BEL cleanly. This is the Anglo-German alliance in action. Confirm you will execute A BEL-BUR."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, I am moving F NTH to BEL this fall to take that center - Germany currently holds it and I intend to seize it. Your A MUN threatening Germany from the south is excellent timing. I propose: you push A MUN toward BER or KIE, I take BEL and threaten HOL from there. Germany will be squeezed from both sides. I have no interest in your home centers or Atlantic coast - my F ENG will stay in the Channel and not threaten BRE. This is the coordinated Anglo-French strike against Germany we discussed. Are you executing A MUN-KIE or A MUN-BER?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, thank you for the continued stability in the north. I am taking BEL this fall with F NTH - Germany has held it too long and is growing dangerous. Your focus on Turkey in the south is wise given Sevastopol's fall. I will continue to respect your Swedish position and NWY remains secure. A weakened Germany benefits us both - their SKA fleet threatens the Baltic which is your concern as much as mine."}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Kaiser, my offer stands: MUN for BEL, firm border at RUH/BUR. I am moving A MUN to BUR this fall as a gesture of good faith - not toward BEL, but to establish the border line. In return I expect you to hold BEL and not press into BUR or beyond. England is maneuvering F NTH toward BEL as we speak - if you lose BEL to England, you lose a center and gain a hostile fleet on your doorstep. We should both be focused on England, not each other. Confirm this arrangement and we can stabilize the west.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, I appreciate the offer but I will not support England into BEL - that simply hands you a center at my expense. What I will do is move A MUN toward the German heartland, threatening BER or KIE directly. If you want to coordinate against Germany, the division should be: England takes HOL (from the sea), France takes BEL and KIE. My F WES is moving toward the Mediterranean as discussed - I have no designs on your Atlantic position. But BEL must come to France, not England, or there is no deal worth making.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, understood - I will keep F WES out of the Tyrrhenian and away from Tunis. You take Tunis and build freely. My fleet moves toward the western Mediterranean to support our shared interests, not to threaten yours. I am pressing Germany from MUN this fall - if you can keep Austria pinned in the Adriatic, we both benefit enormously. Confirm you are moving against Austria and we have a solid partnership going into 1903.'}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, your offer is noted but unacceptable - you want me to hand you BEL while France sits in MUN with 5 centers. I am moving A BEL to BUR and A HOL to RUH this turn to retake Munich. BEL will be empty - take it if you wish, that is your business. But I need you to commit to pressuring France from the west: move F ENG toward MAO or threaten BRE. If you sit idle while I fight France alone, you are no ally at all. France at 5 centers is a greater threat to you than to me - they have SPA, POR, MAR, PAR, BRE and now MUN. Act against them now or watch them dominate the board.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I appreciate your confirmation of non-aggression - I will hold to my end. F SKA moves to DEN this turn, nothing more from me in the north. My full attention is on France: A BEL to BUR, A HOL to RUH, driving toward MUN. I ask only that you keep your units out of SIL and PRU while I deal with this western crisis. Turkey has taken Sevastopol - that is a serious threat to you and I hope you can address it. Once France is contained, German strength will be available to support your interests. Our arrangement remains solid.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, your proposal is insulting. You seized Munich - my home center - and now offer to keep it as a 'settlement.' There is nothing to negotiate. I am coming for MUN with everything I have: A BEL to BUR, A HOL to RUH. You can move A MUN to BUR or BOH - it does not matter, I will pursue you regardless. If you wish to avoid total war, return MUN immediately and we can discuss a real border. Otherwise, I will coordinate with England and Russia to dismantle French gains entirely. The choice is yours, but my armies are already moving."}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your offer is acceptable in principle - withdraw A BUD to GAL immediately and I will not attack you this fall. I will move A SER toward BUD to reclaim my center, and F AEG can pressure Turkey from the south. However, I need to see the withdrawal happen - if A BUD remains in BUD after this phase, I will coordinate with Turkey to crush you from both sides. Vacate BUD, and we have a working arrangement against Turkey. Stay, and you face a two-front war you cannot win.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, I appreciate your honesty about GRE - water under the bridge. Here is my plan this fall: A SER moves to BUD to reclaim my center (Russia has agreed to withdraw to GAL), and F AEG moves to BUL/SC or CON to pressure you - wait, no, I mean F AEG supports A SER or moves to threaten Russia's F RUM via BUL. Let me be direct: I want RUM, you can keep SEV and BUL. Move F SEV to pressure RUM from the north, I'll push from SER. If Russia's A BUD withdraws, I take BUD; if not, I need your A GRE to support A SER into BUD. Confirm: A GRE supports A SER - BUD, F SEV moves toward RUM."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, agreed - ceasefire holds. A VEN stays out of TRI, I stay out of the Adriatic and Venice. Focus your energy westward against France who now has 5 centers and is the biggest threat on the board. I am dealing with Russia and Turkey in the Balkans. One specific request: keep F TUN away from ION/AEG - that sea is mine to operate in. In return, I will not contest your Mediterranean expansion. Let's both grow and deal with the real threats."}]
