[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Excellent work last autumn - your coordination was solid. Now let's execute the next phase. I'm moving F NTH to BEL this spring to finally claim that center, and I need confirmation you're vacating as discussed - A BEL moving out (BUR or elsewhere) so I can walk in cleanly. In return, I'm positioning F ENG to pressure France's Atlantic flank, which should help you retake MUN. France at 6 centers is the primary threat to both of us - let's coordinate to squeeze them. Confirm your moves so we can synchronize."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, let's be direct: you've grown to 6 centers and that makes you the board leader - everyone will be targeting you soon. I'm not interested in a prolonged fight over BEL when we could be coordinating against Germany together. I'm willing to discuss a genuine partition arrangement, but I need to know your actual intentions this spring. Are you moving A KIE south toward Germany, and what's your fleet doing? Give me specifics and I'll give you specifics in return. A Franco-British understanding could be very profitable for both of us."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, our northern non-aggression continues to serve us both well. I'm focused on BEL this spring and have no designs on Sweden or the Baltic. I trust you're continuing to press south against Turkey - their seizure of Sevastopol demands a response. Keep me informed of your situation and I'll do the same. The key threat on the board is France's rapid expansion - worth watching."}]
