[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, the situation is developing well for both of us. Austria's F AEG is a direct threat to my position and your ambitions in the eastern Mediterranean. I propose we coordinate: I will press Austria from the north while you use F ION to threaten AEG or move into the Adriatic to pressure TRI. Austria is overextended holding TRI, BUD, VIE, and GRE simultaneously - they cannot defend everywhere. If you move F ION toward AEG or EAS, it pins their fleet and opens opportunities for both of us. What are your intentions this season? I want to ensure we don't work at cross-purposes."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, let us be direct: we are both threatened by Austria's growing position. AUT holds 4 centers and their F AEG dominates the eastern sea. I propose a temporary understanding - I will not press SEV this season if you focus your forces on BUD and GAL to squeeze Austria from the north. A UKR can move toward RUM or GAL to pressure AUT's eastern flank. I will apply pressure from SER. Austria is the common enemy right now. What do you say to a coordinated anti-Austrian push this season?"}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I want to be transparent with you: Russia is massing against both of us. F SEV threatens my position and A UKR threatens your eastern holdings. I propose we maintain our understanding - I will hold SER and you hold your current position while we both focus on the Russian threat. Your F AEG is well-positioned to support operations. Let us not fight each other while Russia grows to 6 centers. What are your intentions this season?'}]
