GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The situation is clear: France sits at 6 centers with KIE and is the dominant threat to both of us. I hold HOL, BEL, DEN with 5 centers. I propose we coordinate directly this turn. I intend to push A BEL into BUR and A HOL into RUH to squeeze France from the north. If you can pressure France from the west - F ENG toward MAO or threatening BRE - we can crack them open. I am not asking for BEL back; you may hold it if you wish. What I need is your active pressure on France's western flank while I drive east toward MUN. Confirm your intentions and let's coordinate specific moves."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I need your continued non-aggression as I deal with the French menace who seized MUN. I am pushing A BEL-BUR and A HOL-RUH this turn to retake my home center. I ask only that you keep your units out of SIL and PRU - I have no designs on your territory. In return, I will not contest SWE and will support your position in the east. France at 6 centers is a danger to everyone - once I reclaim MUN, the balance is restored. Are we agreed?'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, you hold MUN illegally and have 6 centers - you are the dominant power and every other nation will move against you. I am coming for MUN with everything I have. A BEL-BUR, A HOL-RUH - you cannot hold MUN against this pressure while England threatens your west. Return MUN voluntarily and withdraw to PAR/BRE/MAR and we can discuss a genuine border arrangement. Otherwise you face a two-front war you cannot win. This is your only warning.'}]
