AUT
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Let's be direct: you have A GAL threatening my core, and I have F AEG threatening your southern interests. I propose a genuine standstill this spring - A GAL holds, A BUD holds, no aggression between us. The real threat to both of us is Turkey's 5-center position and France's 6-center dominance in the west. I'm willing to coordinate against Turkey if you give me security in the north - specifically, A GAL withdraws to WAR or holds in place without threatening BUD or VIE. What can you offer me concretely?"}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, I need your help this spring. Russia's A GAL is sitting on my doorstep and I must reclaim BUD. I'm proposing: A BUD - RUM (I take RUM from Russia), A TRI holds, F AEG - BUL/SC (I take BUL). In exchange, I leave SER and CON completely alone and we coordinate against Russia together. If you support my move into RUM with A SER, we split the Balkans cleanly - you keep SER and your Anatolian centers, I take RUM and BUL. Russia at 6 centers is the existential threat to us both. Are you with me?"}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, I want to maintain our ceasefire. A TRI holds, F AEG stays away from ION - I have no interest in fighting you right now. My focus is entirely on Russia and the Balkans. I ask only that you keep A VEN away from TRI and F ION away from AEG. In return I will not move toward Venice or the Adriatic. We both benefit from stability on our shared border while the real threats - Russia at 6 centers, France at 6 centers - grow unchecked.'}]
