RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, let's be direct: my F SEV retook Sevastopol last fall with full support, and you are now isolated in the Black Sea region with no path to expansion northward. I have A GAL positioned and F SEV ready to push into ARM or BLA. However, I am willing to offer a ceasefire: you keep BUL, SER, CON, ANK, SMY - your natural sphere - and I keep SEV, RUM, and the north. We can both profit by turning our attention elsewhere. Austria is weak and Italy is circling them. A RUS-TUR partition of the Balkans is more profitable than this grinding war. Respond with your terms."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I honored my commitment and withdrew A BUD to GAL as promised. Now I need your cooperation: Turkey holds BUL and SER and is threatening both of us. I propose we coordinate against Turkey - I push F SEV into BLA and A UKR toward RUM/BUL while you use your F AEG to pressure BUL from the south. Together we can strip Turkey of their Balkan gains. In return, I will not threaten VIE or BUD this year and will support your position in TRI against Italy. This is a genuine offer - we both benefit from a weaker Turkey.'}, {'recipients': ['GER', 'ENG'], 'body': "Gentlemen, the northern arrangement continues to serve us well. I will hold F SWE in place and have no designs on DEN or NWY this season. My focus is entirely on the southern theater against Turkey. France's seizure of KIE is an outrage that threatens both of you - I hope you are coordinating to push them back. If either of you needs a distraction created elsewhere, let me know. Our mutual non-aggression remains firm."}]
