[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I appreciate that you withdrew from BUD - that builds trust. Here are my concrete moves this spring: A BUD moves toward RUM, A TRI holds, F AEG pressures BUL from the south. I need you to hold A GAL in place and not threaten VIE or BUD - that is the price of my cooperation against Turkey. If you move F SEV into BLA and push A UKR toward RUM, we can coordinate a joint squeeze on Turkey's Balkan position. But I will not commit to anti-Turkey action if A GAL is still a dagger at my throat. Hold GAL, and we have a deal."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, I hear you on Russia being the threat, but I need to be honest: my moves this spring are A BUD - RUM and F AEG - BUL/SC. I am taking RUM from Russia and pressuring BUL. I am not attacking SER or CON - those are yours. If you want to coordinate, support my A BUD - RUM with A SER, and I will ensure F AEG does not threaten your Anatolian centers. We can divide the Balkans: you keep SER and your home centers, I take RUM and BUL. Russia at 6 centers is the real enemy - let's both grow at their expense rather than fight each other."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, I accept your proposal: keep A VEN in TYR and F ION moving east, and I will hold A TRI and keep F AEG away from ION. Our border stays quiet. I am focused entirely on Russia and the Balkans this season - RUM and BUL are my targets. If you want to coordinate against Turkey in the eastern Mediterranean, F ION pushing toward EAS while F AEG pressures from the north could be mutually beneficial. Let's stay out of each other's way and both grow."}]
