TUR
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, I agree - let's coordinate precisely. I will move A SER to GRE this spring to pressure Austria's Balkan position, while you move F ION toward AEG or EAS to pin their fleet. This splits Austria's attention and opens their centers to both of us. My A CON will move to BUL to consolidate. Austria cannot defend everywhere - TRI, BUD, GRE simultaneously. After we weaken them, we can discuss dividing their centers fairly. Confirm you are moving F ION to AEG or EAS this turn."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I accept your ceasefire proposal in principle - grinding war benefits neither of us while Austria and the western powers grow. I will not press SEV this season. In return, I ask that you keep F SEV out of ARM and BLA - let us maintain a buffer. I propose we both focus pressure on Austria: you push A GAL toward VIE or BUD, I apply pressure from SER. Austria at 4 centers with Italy circling them is the real opportunity. Let us formalize this: TUR keeps BUL, SER, CON, ANK, SMY; RUS keeps SEV, RUM, and northern centers. Agreed?'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I must be honest: your proposal to take BUL is unacceptable - BUL is my center and I will defend it. However, I have no interest in fighting you when Russia holds 6 centers and threatens us both. I propose a genuine ceasefire: I hold SER, you hold your current position, and we both focus on Russia. F AEG should move to support operations against Russia rather than threatening my centers. If you move F AEG toward BUL, we are at war and Italy will exploit your exposed TRI. Choose wisely.'}]
