ITA
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, let us be specific: I will move F ION to GRE this spring, taking Austria's supply center. I need you to move A SER to support pressure on Austria's Balkan flank - if A SER threatens BUD or holds to pin Austrian forces, Austria cannot reinforce GRE. You benefit by weakening Austria's grip on the Balkans, and I gain GRE. This is a clean coordination - I take GRE, you press BUD. Confirm you will not move into GRE yourself and we have a deal."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I hear your proposal for continued ceasefire and I am genuinely considering it - Russia at 6 centers and France at 6 centers are the real threats to both of us. However, I must be honest: Turkey is pressuring me hard to coordinate against you, and I need something concrete to resist that pressure. If you can offer me a path to a supply center in the east - perhaps acknowledging my claim on TUN expansion or supporting a future move against Turkey - I can hold F ION back from GRE and keep A VEN away from TRI. Without something tangible, I may be forced to act against you simply to keep pace with the other great powers. What can you offer?'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, I am moving F ION to GRE this spring to strike Austria's Mediterranean position - this is confirmed. A VEN will move to TYR to maintain pressure and flexibility. I need you to push toward MUN or threaten VIE to ensure Austria cannot concentrate forces against me in the south. Russia's 6 centers concerns me greatly - once we have dealt with Austria, we must discuss how to contain Russia before they dominate the board. Keep F WES out of Tyrrhenian as promised and we remain aligned."}]
