ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Confirmed - I'm moving F NTH to BEL this spring to claim it, and F ENG toward MAO to pressure France's Atlantic flank exactly as you requested. This squeezes France from both sides. Your A BEL-BUR and A HOL-RUH push is the right move - let's crack France open together. With BEL secured by England and you driving toward MUN, France's 6-center lead becomes a liability. Execute your moves and I'll execute mine - this is the turn we start dismantling French dominance."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, your proposal to partition Germany is interesting but premature - Germany still has 5 centers and won't fold easily without coordinated pressure. Here's what I can offer: I'll move F ENG toward MAO to signal I'm not threatening your Atlantic position, and I'll consider the anti-German coordination you propose. However, I need you to confirm A KIE moves toward BER this turn as a show of good faith. If you execute that move, we can discuss the full partition arrangement for autumn. My F NTH is moving to BEL - that's non-negotiable as it's been contested too long - but I have no designs on your home centers."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, our arrangement remains solid. I'm taking BEL this spring and positioning against France - they're the board leader and need to be checked. Your focus on Turkey is exactly right; their seizure of Sevastopol cannot stand. One thing worth noting: France at 6 centers with KIE is a long-term threat to everyone, including Russia's western flank. If you have any opportunity to signal displeasure with French expansion, it would benefit us all. Our northern non-aggression continues - I have no Baltic ambitions."}]
