[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I accept your standstill proposal with one condition: A GAL holds in place (no move toward BUD or VIE), and in return you hold A BUD in place and do not move F AEG against my interests. My F SEV will push into BLA this turn to pressure Turkey, and A UKR will support that move. Turkey holds SER adjacent to your territory - they are the greater threat to both of us. If you use F AEG to pressure BUL from the south while I push from the north via BLA, we can strip Turkey of BUL this year. Concrete proposal: I hold A GAL, you hold A BUD, we both press Turkey. Agreed?'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, your proposal to coordinate against Austria is noted, but I see through it - you want me to expose my flank while you consolidate. Here is the reality: I have F SEV ready to enter BLA, A UKR in support, and A GAL threatening your ally's flank. If you want peace, withdraw A CON to SMY and acknowledge RUM and SEV as Russian spheres permanently. Otherwise I push into BLA this turn and you will find yourself fighting on two fronts as Austria and I coordinate against you. The choice is yours - a negotiated settlement now, or war."}, {'recipients': ['ENG', 'GER'], 'body': 'England, Germany - France at 6 centers with KIE and SPA is the dominant threat on the board. I strongly encourage you both to coordinate a joint squeeze: England push from the north, Germany retake MUN and push west. I will maintain my non-aggression commitments fully - F SWE stays out of your affairs. Once France is contained, we can discuss a stable northern arrangement. Do not let France reach 7 or 8 centers unchecked.'}]
