ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "The spring results were excellent - you took BER from France, and I secured BEL as planned. France is now dangerously overextended with 6 centers and units scattered. I propose we continue coordinating: I will hold BEL and can support your moves to retake BER or push into BUR. My F ENG can move to MAO to threaten France's Atlantic flank (BRE, POR). What are your intentions this fall? I want to ensure we don't accidentally clash while squeezing France from both sides."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, you've made impressive gains but you're now the board leader and everyone will target you. I hold BEL and have no intention of giving it up - that's simply reality. However, I have no desire for a prolonged Anglo-French war. Germany is your real threat on the continent - they want BER back and will push hard. I can keep pressure off your northern flank if you focus on Germany. What are your intentions this fall? Let's avoid unnecessary conflict between us."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, the board is developing well for both of us. France has surged to 6 centers and is the clear leader - I'd encourage you to consider whether any pressure westward is possible. I'm consolidating in BEL and positioning to threaten France's Atlantic position. Germany is fighting France on the continent which suits us both. Are you still focused southward against Turkey/Austria? Just want to ensure we remain coordinated in the north."}]
