[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The situation is clear: France holds BER, Germany holds KIE with their army. I intend to move A BER to MUN this fall, striking deep into Germany's heartland. Germany is caught between us - you hold BEL, I hold BER. I propose you move F BEL to support any pressure on HOL or RUH while I take MUN. Together we can reduce Germany to 2-3 centers this year. What are your fleet dispositions? I need to know if F ENG is moving to threaten HOL or staying put. France remains committed to our anti-German partnership - let's finish the job."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, your position is dire. I hold BER, England holds BEL, and your armies are scattered. I offer you one chance at a negotiated settlement: cede MUN to France and I will support you in retaking BEL from England. You keep DEN, HOL, KIE - a viable 3-center Germany. Refuse, and I take MUN this fall while England squeezes from the west. The choice is yours, but decide quickly.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, France is pressing hard into Germany - A BER moves to MUN this fall. I need your A TYR to move toward MUN as well to ensure the capture - can you support or move into MUN from TYR? This would give us both leverage over central Europe and weaken Germany decisively. In return, I will keep F WES out of the Tyrrhenian and support your position against Austria. What are your plans for TYR this fall?'}]
