TUR
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "The situation is developing well. AUT's F AEG bounced off BUL last spring - my A CON moved to BUL and held it, while A SER took GRE. AUT is now exposed and weakened. I propose we coordinate directly: I will hold GRE and BUL firmly while you press AUT from the west through TRI and the Adriatic. AUT has F AEG, A BUD, and A VIE - if you push A TYR toward TRI and use F TUN to threaten ION/AEG, I can press from the east. AUT cannot defend on two fronts. What are your intended moves this fall?"}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, your F AEG attempted to take BUL last spring - that is an act of war I cannot ignore. However, I am a pragmatic man. I hold GRE and BUL; you hold TRI and VIE. We are bleeding each other while Russia sits at 6 centers and grows stronger. I propose an immediate ceasefire: F AEG withdraws from the Aegean, I keep GRE and BUL, and we both turn our attention to the real threat - Russia's A GAL and F BLA pressing down on both of us. If you refuse, I will coordinate with Italy to dismantle your position entirely. Your choice."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, we have been at odds but the strategic picture demands we reassess. Austria has 4 centers and is squeezed between us - they are the weakest power in our region. I propose a temporary understanding: I will not press toward SEV or RUM this season if you do not move F BLA into CON or BUL. Let us both focus on Austria's collapse. Your A GAL can press BUD while I hold the Balkans. Once Austria is eliminated, we can negotiate a fair division of their centers. What say you?"}]
