GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The situation is exactly as we planned - France overextended and now holds KIE and BER with isolated units. My moves this fall: F DEN supports A KIE (I'm already in KIE with my army), and I push to retake BER. I need you to hold BEL firmly and keep pressure on France from the west - F ENG toward MAO or threatening BRE keeps France from reinforcing. France is at 6 centers and must be cut down now before they snowball. Confirm you're holding BEL and pressing France westward - together we dismantle them."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, the board is developing well for both of us. France has overreached with 6 centers and occupies my home territories - I am moving aggressively to retake BER and consolidate. I ask only that you continue to hold F SWE and stay out of DEN and the Baltic - our non-aggression pact has served us both well. With France as the common threat to European stability, I trust you see the value in letting Germany reassert itself in the west. Any pressure you can apply on Austria or Turkey in the east keeps them occupied and away from my flanks.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, you have made a grave miscalculation. You hold KIE and BER with isolated armies surrounded by hostile forces - England presses from the west, I retake from the east. Your 6-center empire is a house of cards. I offer you one chance: withdraw from BER and KIE immediately and return to your natural borders, and I will not pursue you further west. Refuse, and I will coordinate with England and Russia to systematically dismantle everything you have built. The choice is yours, but choose quickly.'}]
