RUS
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "The situation has developed well for both of us. My F BLA is now positioned to threaten Turkey's northern flank directly - I can move on ANK or CON while your F AEG presses from the south. I propose we coordinate a joint squeeze on Turkey this fall: I move F BLA toward ANK or CON, you move F AEG into BUL or support an attack there. A GAL remains in place as agreed - I have no designs on BUD or VIE this turn. Turkey is the common enemy and now is the moment to strike while they are weak. What is your intended move with F AEG?"}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, your position is deteriorating. You hold BUL and SER but Austria's F AEG threatens BUL from the south and my F BLA threatens ANK and CON from the north. You are caught in a vice. I offer you one chance to negotiate: withdraw A CON to SMY and acknowledge RUM and the Black Sea as Russian spheres, and I will hold F BLA in place this turn rather than attacking. Refuse, and I move on ANK immediately with Austrian coordination on BUL. The choice is yours - a managed retreat or a catastrophic loss."}, {'recipients': ['GER', 'ENG'], 'body': "Northern front remains stable and I intend to keep it that way. F SWE holds in place - no moves toward DEN or NWY. I am focused entirely on the southern theater against Turkey. France's dominance in the west with 6 centers including KIE and BER is the real threat to both of you - I hope you are coordinating to contain them. Let me know if there is anything I can do to support your western efforts diplomatically."}]
