AUT
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'The spring results were frustrating for both of us - my A BUD bounced off your A UKR in RUM, and your A UKR bounced as well. Neither of us gained anything. I propose we coordinate properly this fall: I will move A BUD - RUM with support from A VIE if you withdraw A UKR away from RUM. In exchange, I will hold A VIE away from GAL and we can focus our combined pressure on Turkey, who now holds GRE (my supply center) and is growing dangerously. Turkey at 5 centers with SER and GRE is a bigger threat to both of us than our current standoff. Let A GAL hold or move north, let me take RUM, and we can squeeze Turkey together. What do you say?'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, you now occupy GRE which is my supply center - this is unacceptable and I will be moving to retake it. However, I want to offer you a deal rather than open war: if you withdraw A GRE back to SER or ALB this fall, I will not press F AEG into BUL or CON, and we can maintain a working relationship. I have F AEG positioned to take BUL, CON, or SMY - I would rather not use it against you if we can reach an agreement. Russia is the common threat with 6 centers. Consider: you give back GRE, I leave BUL alone, and we both focus on containing Russia. If you refuse, I will take BUL with F AEG and contest every Turkish center in the Aegean. Your choice.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, our ceasefire has held well and I appreciate A VEN moving to TYR rather than threatening Trieste. I want to continue our cooperation. This fall I am focused on reclaiming GRE from Turkey and potentially taking RUM from Russia - I have no designs on Italian territory. I would ask that A TYR remain in TYR or move toward BOH/MUN rather than toward TRI or VIE, and F TUN stays away from AEG. In return, I will keep my units away from VEN and the Adriatic. Turkey is becoming a serious threat with 5 centers - if you have any ability to pressure them from the south via ION or EAS, that would benefit us both. Can we confirm this arrangement?'}]
