ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Confirmed - I am holding BEL firmly and F ENG will move toward MAO to threaten France's Atlantic flank. This keeps pressure on BRE and POR while you retake BER. France is dangerously overextended and this is the moment to cut them down. I will not move against HOL or any German territory - our coordination remains solid. Let's dismantle France together this fall."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, I appreciate the offer but I must be direct: I am holding BEL and F ENG is moving to MAO - not to support your push into HOL, but to secure my own Atlantic position. Germany is retaking BER this fall and you will be squeezed hard on the continent. If you want to avoid being crushed between Germany and England, now is the time to negotiate seriously - I am open to a genuine arrangement, but it requires you to acknowledge my hold on BEL and offer something concrete in return. What can you actually offer me?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, thank you for the continued stability in the north - much appreciated. France at 6 centers with BER and KIE is the board's dominant threat and Germany and I are coordinating to contain them this fall. Your diplomatic pressure on France from the east would be valuable - even just signaling that Russia is watching their expansion could help. Keep me informed of your southern progress against Turkey."}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, my moves this fall are locked in: A KIE moves to BER to retake my capital, F DEN supports A KIE to hold KIE secure, and A RUH holds or presses toward MUN. France's A BER is isolated and unsupported - if you can apply any pressure from BEL toward BUR or hold BEL firmly, France cannot reinforce BER and I retake it cleanly. F ENG toward MAO is exactly right - threaten BRE and POR to keep France's attention divided. We are on the verge of breaking France's overextension. Do not waver."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your restraint in the north is appreciated and I will honor our arrangement - F DEN stays clear of SWE. I am moving A KIE to BER this fall to retake my capital from France. With England pressing from the west and me from the east, France will be forced back to their natural borders within two turns. Your continued focus on the south is wise - Turkey and Austria are the prizes there. Our non-aggression pact remains firm and mutually beneficial.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, your offer is contemptible - you want me to surrender MUN in exchange for help against England? You hold my home capital BER with a single isolated army while England occupies BEL and I hold KIE with a supported army. Your position is the one that is untenable. This fall I retake BER, and England dismantles your western flank. There is no negotiated settlement where Germany surrenders its heartland. Prepare to be rolled back.'}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, confirmed: A TYR will move to TRI this fall. I know that contradicts what I said before, but hear me out - Turkey holds GRE, BUL, SER, and is pressing you hard from the south while Russia sits in GAL. You cannot hold on all fronts. I am taking TRI to relieve pressure on you by forcing Turkey to worry about Italian naval power in the Adriatic. F TUN moves to ION to threaten GRE directly. This is not a stab - it is a reorientation of forces. If you resist, we both lose to Turkey and Russia. If you accept, I will use TRI as a staging ground against Turkey, not against VIE or BUD. Think carefully.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, your proposal to coordinate against Austria is noted, but I need something concrete before I commit. You hold GRE - that center should be mine given my position. Here is my offer: support my F TUN moving to ION, and I will use ION to pressure AEG rather than contest GRE this season. But if you refuse and keep GRE while asking me to do your dirty work against Austria, I will coordinate with Austria to push you back. A TYR moves toward TRI this fall regardless - the question is whether Italy and Turkey are working together or against each other afterward.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, I cannot move A TYR to MUN this fall - I need it pressing toward TRI to keep Austria off balance and secure the Adriatic. Moving to MUN would expose my flank entirely. However, I confirm F WES must stay out of TYS and MAR must not threaten PIE - hold to that and I will continue pinning Austria from the west. Your A BER to MUN is a strong move; GER is collapsing and you should press that advantage. Just leave the Mediterranean and Italian home centers entirely to me and we have no quarrel.'}]
