RUS
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I reject your proposal to hand you RUM - that is a Russian supply center and non-negotiable. However, I am open to genuine coordination against Turkey. Here is what I will actually do this fall: F BLA moves to ANK or CON to strike Turkey directly, A UKR supports F BLA or moves to RUM to hold it, A GAL holds as agreed. I am not withdrawing from RUM. If you want to coordinate against Turkey, move F AEG into BUL - that is the useful contribution. Turkey holds GRE which is your center; take it back by pressuring BUL. We both gain from Turkey's collapse. But I will not surrender RUM as the price of your cooperation."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, your offer to coordinate against Austria is transparent maneuvering - you want me to expose my flank while you consolidate. I am not interested. My F BLA moves this fall and you should consider carefully where it lands. If you want to avoid catastrophic losses, the only acceptable arrangement is: A CON holds in place, A GRE holds in place, and you acknowledge RUM and BLA as Russian spheres permanently. Any aggressive move by you this turn will be met with an immediate strike on ANK. I have Austrian coordination on BUL from the south. Your position is untenable - accept these terms or face the consequences.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG', 'GER'], 'body': 'Confirmed - F SWE holds in place, no moves toward DEN or the Baltic. I am striking south against Turkey this fall with F BLA. France at 6 centers with KIE and BER is indeed the dominant threat to European stability - I trust you are both coordinating to retake those German home centers and contain French expansion. Germany retaking BER and KIE would rebalance the west considerably. I support your efforts diplomatically and will keep the eastern front occupied so neither AUT nor TUR can interfere with your western campaign.'}]
