[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, I hear you on the board leader concern - but consider: Germany still has 5 centers and is the immediate threat to both of us. My move this fall is A BER to MUN, striking Germany's heartland. I need you to move F BEL to HOL or support pressure on RUH to prevent Germany from reinforcing MUN. If we coordinate now, Germany drops to 3 centers and we both gain. I have no designs on BEL - it's yours. Let's finish Germany off together this fall, then we can discuss the broader balance. Confirm F BEL moves to HOL and we have a deal."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, confirmed: F WES stays out of TYS entirely - the Mediterranean is yours to dominate. I have no interest in your home centers. My focus is Germany - A BER moves to MUN this fall. I understand A TYR is moving toward TRI or VIE, which is excellent for keeping Austria pinned. One request: if you can spare any pressure toward MUN from TYR, even a feint, it helps ensure Germany cannot reinforce. Otherwise, press Austria hard - the more they're distracted, the better for both of us. Our arrangement stands firm."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, your threats ring hollow. You have 3 armies against my position in BER and England pressing BEL. I am not withdrawing - I am advancing. A BER moves to MUN this fall. Your only rational move is to accept the settlement I offered: cede MUN, keep DEN, HOL, KIE. A 3-center Germany survives. A Germany that fights France AND England simultaneously does not. This is your final opportunity for a negotiated outcome - after this fall, the terms will be far worse.'}]
