TUR
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, I understand your frustration - you are right that I moved to GRE myself last spring. But consider the math: I hold GRE, BUL, SER, ANK, CON, SMY - six centers. Austria has F AEG threatening me from the south, Russia threatens from the north. I am not your enemy, I am your opportunity. Here is my concrete offer: I will support your F TUN into ION this fall, clearing the path for you to press AUT's position in the Adriatic. In return, I need you to move F TUN toward ION and A TYR toward TRI - not toward GRE. GRE is mine this season; TRI is yours for the taking. AUT cannot defend TRI while I hold the Balkans. Once AUT collapses, we divide their centers fairly - TRI and VIE to you, BUD to me. This is worth far more than GRE alone. Do we have a deal?"}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, your ultimatum changes nothing. You cannot retake GRE while defending TRI from Italy's A TYR and your own overextended position. F AEG is one fleet against my two armies plus Italian pressure from the west. I am not withdrawing from GRE. However, I will make you one final offer: accept the current lines - GRE to me, BUL to me, TRI and VIE to you - and we both turn on Russia together. Your A BUD presses GAL, my A GRE presses SER toward BUD as a feint to draw Russian attention, and we coordinate. Russia at 6 centers is the existential threat to both of us. If you attack me instead, Italy takes TRI while you are distracted and you lose everything. Choose wisely."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your offer of a managed retreat is insulting and I reject it entirely. I will not withdraw to SMY and I will not concede the Black Sea. However, I note that Austria is the weakest power in our region with only 4 centers and units spread thin. My proposal stands: I hold my current position, you hold yours, and we both press Austria this fall. Your A GAL into BUD is a powerful move - I will not interfere with it. Once Austria collapses, we negotiate the Balkans from a position of mutual strength rather than mutual exhaustion. Attacking me now only benefits Italy and the western powers who are watching us bleed each other. Think strategically.'}]
