[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, the board situation is clear: France holds BER with 6 centers, Germany is reduced to KIE, RUH, and DEN with 4 centers. This is the moment to finish Germany together. I propose: A BER moves to MUN (taking Germany's heartland), while England uses F BEL to pressure HOL or DEN. Germany cannot defend on all fronts. Once Germany is eliminated or crippled, we can discuss a stable partition of their remaining centers - I take MUN/BER, you take HOL/DEN. France has no designs on BEL or English home centers. What say you - shall we end Germany this year?"}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, your position is untenable. You hold KIE, RUH, and DEN with 4 centers while France sits in BER and England holds BEL. I am moving A BER to MUN this turn - you cannot stop it. However, I offer you this: if you order A KIE to hold and A RUH to hold, I will not pursue further German centers this year and we can negotiate a settlement. Fight me and you will be eliminated. Accept this and you survive. The choice is yours.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, France continues to respect our arrangement - F MAO stays out of the Mediterranean and I have no designs on your home centers. I am pressing hard against Germany in the north. I note Russia has 8 centers and is the dominant eastern power - AUT, TUR, and yourself should be coordinating to check Russian expansion before it becomes unstoppable. I am happy to discuss how France can support your eastern ambitions diplomatically. What are your plans this season?'}]
