[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The attack on BER succeeded - France's A BER is now sitting isolated in my capital with no support. I need your continued pressure from the west. My plan this turn: A KIE - BER (supported by F DEN), A RUH - MUN to secure my home centers. France has A BER and A GAS with F MAO - they are overextended. If you move F BEL toward BUR or threaten PAR, France cannot reinforce BER and I retake my capital. We are close to breaking France entirely. Hold BEL, press westward, and let's finish this together. Once France is neutralized, we can discuss dividing their centers fairly."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Our non-aggression pact continues to serve us both well. I am focused entirely on retaking BER from France this turn - A KIE - BER with F DEN support. I have no designs on SWE or the Baltic. France at 6 centers is a threat to everyone - I trust you see the value in letting me crush them in the west while you consolidate your impressive eastern gains. I will keep F DEN away from SWE as promised. All I ask is that you continue to stay out of SIL and PRU.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "Your position is collapsing. You hold BER with a single unsupported army, England presses from the west, and I am driving A KIE - BER with fleet support. You cannot hold BER, MUN is exposed, and your Atlantic flank is threatened by England's fleet. I offer you one chance: withdraw A BER to SIL voluntarily and I will not pursue you further east this year. Refuse, and I take BER by force and coordinate with England to dismantle your entire position. The choice is yours."}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, the results speak for themselves: I took ANK, you took SER, and Turkey is now squeezed between us. I hold BUD, RUM, and ANK - Turkey holds CON, GRE, BUL, SMY. My proposal: I move F ANK to CON (taking it) while A RUM moves to BUL, and you move F AEG to support or take GRE/BUL from the south. We split Turkey's remaining centers between us. I will give you SER and TRI if you cooperate - I want CON, BUL, and SMY. In exchange, I will withdraw A BUD to GAL this turn to demonstrate good faith. Respond with your intended moves so we can coordinate precisely."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, your position is desperate: I hold ANK, A RUM threatens BUL, Austria's F AEG threatens from the Aegean. You have CON and GRE as your only remaining units. I offer you this: surrender CON peacefully and I will support you in retaining SMY and GRE as a rump state. Resist and Austria and I will eliminate you entirely within two turns. The choice is yours - a dignified retreat or total annihilation."}, {'recipients': ['ENG', 'GER'], 'body': 'Friends, I am fully engaged eliminating Turkey in the south and have no interest in northern adventures. F SWE will hold this turn - I ask only that you continue to focus your energies westward against France, who now holds 6 centers including BER. France is the dominant threat on the board and must be contained. I remain committed to our northern non-aggression arrangement.'}]
