[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "The situation has clarified dramatically. Russia now holds ANK (my home center!) with F ANK, and AUT has F AEG threatening my position. I need your help urgently. F ION can move to AEG to neutralize Austria's fleet - this directly benefits you by opening the Adriatic and Ionian for Italian expansion. Meanwhile I will move A GRE to SER (taking an Austrian center) and A CON to BUL to consolidate. If you move F ION to AEG, Austria cannot threaten either of us from the sea. I offer you a free hand in TRI, VEN area and will not contest any Italian gains in the western Balkans. This is the moment to strike Austria while they are overextended."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, we are both being consumed by Russia. Look at the board: RUS holds BUD, ANK, RUM, SWE - 8 centers and growing. They have taken my home center of ANK. I propose an immediate ceasefire between us. I will not attack SER if you move F AEG away from my territory. Together we can coordinate: your A SER supports my push toward RUM, my A GRE holds the southern flank. If we fight each other, Russia wins everything. Name your terms for a temporary truce - I am listening.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'You hold ANK, my home center. This is an act of war that cannot stand. However, I am a pragmatist. If you return ANK and withdraw F ANK to BLA, I will accept the current partition: you keep RUM and BUD, I keep CON, SMY, BUL, GRE. We establish a clear border and turn our attention to the real threats - AUT and the western powers are growing unchecked. If you refuse, I will dedicate every resource to making your southern position untenable. The choice is yours: profitable peace or costly war.'}]
