[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, we are aligned. My orders this phase: A GRE moves to SER (taking Austria's center) and A CON moves to BUL (consolidating my position). You move F ION to AEG - this neutralizes Austria's fleet entirely and opens the Adriatic for you. With F AEG eliminated, Austria collapses. I take SER and BUD, you take TRI and VEN. Russia is the long-term threat but Austria must fall first. Execute F ION-AEG and A TYR-TRI. We divide the Balkans as agreed."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I accept your proposal for coordination against Russia. I will move A GRE to ALB as a gesture of good faith, freeing GRE for your consideration, and A CON to BUL to press northward. In return, commit F AEG to support my BUL position and hold A SER. Russia at 8 centers destroys us both if we fight each other. This is your last chance for a real alliance - take it or Italy's F ION moves to AEG and you lose your fleet regardless."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your ultimatum is rejected. I will not surrender CON. You hold ANK temporarily but overextend yourself - France holds BER, Germany presses from the north, and the western powers will not allow your dominance. I am not eliminated while I hold units. My terms stand: return ANK, accept the partition, and we both profit. If you press south, you invite a coalition against you that will cost you far more than ANK is worth. Think carefully.'}]
