[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I accept your ceasefire terms. A BUD will hold in place this turn - I will not move it toward VIE or TRI. A RUM will move to BUL to pressure Turkey from the north, and F ANK will move to CON. You should move F AEG to support or take GRE. This coordinated push eliminates Turkey quickly. Once Turkey is gone, we can negotiate a fair division of their centers. I need CON and BUL; you can have GRE and SMY. Confirm your F AEG move and we proceed together.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, your offer is rejected. ANK is mine and I will not return it. I am moving F ANK to CON this turn and A RUM to BUL simultaneously. Austria's F AEG closes from the south. You have no path to survival through resistance - your two units cannot hold against this coordinated assault. If you wish to negotiate the terms of your elimination rather than fight it, I am willing to discuss which power inherits SMY. Otherwise, prepare to be removed from the board entirely."}, {'recipients': ['ENG', 'GER'], 'body': 'Confirmed: F SWE holds this turn, no northern moves from me. I am fully committed to eliminating Turkey in the south this season - F ANK moves to CON, A RUM moves to BUL. France at 6 centers is indeed the dominant western threat and I support your efforts to contain them. GER, your A KIE to BER push has my full endorsement - retake your home center. ENG, press France from the Atlantic. The northern arrangement holds firm.'}]
