[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, we are aligned. My moves this season: F ION to AEG (neutralizing Austria's fleet and opening the eastern Med), A TYR to TRI (taking the center Austria cannot defend). You move A GRE to SER and A CON to BUL as you proposed - this collapses Austria entirely. After this season, Austria is finished and we divide the Balkans: TRI and VIE to Italy, BUD and SER to Turkey. Russia is the next target. Execute your moves and I will execute mine."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I have considered your proposal carefully. I cannot hold TYR indefinitely while Russia devours your eastern centers - BUD is already gone, ANK is Russian. The honest truth: I am moving A TYR to TRI and F ION to AEG. This is not personal - it is strategic necessity. With TRI I can build and contribute real force against Russia. Your F AEG is isolated and cannot hold. Surrender TRI peacefully and redirect A VIE and A SER against Russia - that is the only path that saves you from elimination. Fight me and we both lose to Moscow.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, I am moving aggressively this season: F ION to AEG, A TYR to TRI. Austria collapses. Turkey is coordinating with me against Austria and then Russia. I need you to maintain pressure on Germany so no units flow south to complicate my Balkan push. Russia at 8 centers is the endgame threat - once I secure TRI and build, I can contribute meaningfully to checking them. Keep F MAO out of the Mediterranean and we remain on excellent terms. The western and eastern theaters must stay separate.'}]
