[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, my moves are confirmed: A KIE - BER supported by F DEN, and A RUH - MUN to secure my home center against France's threatened advance. France claims they are moving A BER - MUN this turn - if true, BER will be empty when I arrive and MUN will bounce them back. Either way I retake BER or hold MUN. Your job: keep F BEL in place to hold the western flank and move F ENG toward MAO to threaten BRE. France cannot fight on three fronts. After this turn France drops to 5 centers or fewer and we can begin dismantling them systematically. Stay the course - we are winning."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, confirmed: F DEN stays away from SWE, I am fully committed to the western campaign against France. A KIE - BER with F DEN support this turn - France's isolated army in my capital will be expelled. I appreciate your continued restraint in SIL and PRU. France at 6 centers is the board's greatest threat and I intend to break them this turn. Once France is contained, we should discuss the future shape of Europe - I believe our interests remain complementary."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, your bluff is transparent. You claim A BER - MUN, but if you move out of BER you hand me my capital for free, and A RUH will contest MUN. If you hold BER, A KIE - BER with F DEN support overwhelms you 2-to-1. You have no good move. England presses from the west, I press from the east - your position is finished. Withdraw from German territory entirely and perhaps we negotiate a ceasefire on the Rhine. Continue this futile resistance and I will coordinate your complete elimination with England and Russia.'}]
