[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, your offer is acceptable in principle. I will move F AEG to GRE this turn to take that center from Turkey, and A SER holds to maintain position. If you genuinely withdraw A BUD to GAL as promised, that demonstrates good faith and we can coordinate the Turkey dismemberment next turn. I expect A BUD-GAL and A RUM holds this phase. Do not move A BUD toward VIE or TRI - that would end any cooperation immediately. Let's split Turkey: you take CON and ANK, I take GRE and BUL."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, I hear your ceasefire proposal but I need a center to survive - Russia holds BUD and I am at 3 centers. I will take GRE with F AEG this turn; that is non-negotiable for my survival. However, I offer this: A SER will NOT move to BUL, and I will not support any Russian move into BUL or CON. After I take GRE, we can discuss coordinating A GRE (now mine) to support your defense of BUL against Russia's A RUM. Russia is the real enemy - once I have GRE secured, I am willing to hold there and turn against Russia with you."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, I will not give you TRI - that is my home center and non-negotiable. However, I accept a ceasefire on all other fronts: A TYR to BOH (pressures Russia's flank as you suggest), F ION stays out of AEG. In return, A VIE will not threaten you and I focus entirely on Turkey and Russia. If you move A TYR to TRI, I will dedicate A VIE to bouncing you and we both lose while Russia wins. Move to BOH and we both gain. This is the last reasonable offer I make."}]
