[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, I hear your concerns and I will be direct: France is moving A BER to MUN this turn to cripple Germany - this is happening regardless. F MAO holds in the Atlantic and A GAS holds in place. I am not threatening BEL or your home centers. What I offer is this: Germany is your real problem on the continent, not France. If you coordinate F BEL to pressure HOL while I take MUN, Germany collapses to 2-3 centers and we both gain. I will commit to no moves against BEL this year. But if you coordinate with Germany against me, you simply hand Russia and Austria a free hand in the east while we bleed each other - that serves no one. Join me against Germany now, and we can discuss a stable partition afterward.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, your bluster is noted but your position is fantasy. A KIE cannot take BER without support, and you have no fleet to provide it from BAL. A BER is moving to MUN this turn - your heartland falls. A RUH cannot stop it. Your only rational move is to accept the inevitable and negotiate terms before you are eliminated entirely. I am not interested in your destruction if you cooperate - hold your remaining units and we discuss a ceasefire after MUN changes hands. Fight me and England simultaneously and you will have nothing left by winter.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, I am executing A BER to MUN this turn to break Germany. F MAO holds and A GAS holds - no threat to you whatsoever. Russia at 8 centers is the board's dominant threat and I strongly urge you to coordinate with Austria and Turkey to check them in the Balkans before it is too late. France will support your eastern ambitions diplomatically and can apply pressure from the north once Germany is finished. Our arrangement stands firm - I have no Mediterranean ambitions that threaten you."}]
